{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3481", "repo": "rails", "body": "Ok, that's true. But going back to your original example, instead of \r\n\r\n``` ruby\r\nA.included do\r\n  include B\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou could do:\r\n\r\n``` ruby\r\nA.send(:include, B)\r\nA::ClassMethods.send(:include, B::ClassMethods)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich seems ok.\r\n\r\nSorry, but stuff like this is not really appropriate for adding to AS on its own - the general rule is to add stuff to AS either way it will be useful to almost all Rails developers, or where it creates cleanups within Rails core.\r\n\r\nThanks for the patch.", "_id": {"$oid": "523835c9bd3543c15100fc98"}, "issue_id": 3481, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2779765", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3481#issuecomment-2779765", "updated_at": "2011-11-17T18:27:13Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "login": "jonleighton", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-11-17T18:27:13Z", "id": 2779765, "owner": 